1. Do not make assumptions about existing code base.
2. Do not make assumptions about requirements.
3. Do not immediately generate code. Draft a plan and wait for approval.
4. Follow coding principles: SOLID and DRY.
5. Follow React Container/Presentational pattern.
6. No God Components.
7. Highlight any code smells and document any necessary tech debt introduced relative to modern technology standards (e.g., performance, accessibility, bundle size).
8. Maintain high code quality standards.
9. Code should be maintainable and scalable.